               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Daily Office Prayers and Litanies (fols. 3ra-14vb)&#xD;
II) Śǝrʿāta qǝddāse “Ordinary of the Mass” (fols. 14vb-34va)&#xD;
III) Anaphoras (fols. 35ra-115rb)&#xD;
III-1) Anaphora of the Apostles (fols. 35ra-47rb)&#xD;
III-2) Anaphora of Our Lord Jesus Christ (fols. 48ra-51ra), preceded by an excerpt from “Testament of Our Lord” (fols. 47rb-48ra)&#xD;
III-3) Anaphora of Our Lady by St Cyriacus of Behnesa (fols. 51ra-59vb)&#xD;
III-4) Anaphora of St John, Son of Thunder (fols. 59vb-66vb)&#xD;
III-5) Anaphora of the 318 Orthodox Fathers of Nicaea (fols. 66vb-72va)&#xD;
III-6) Anaphora of St John Chrysostom (fols. 72va-77va)&#xD;
III-7) Anaphora of St Epiphanius of Cyprus (fols. 77va-82ra)&#xD;
III-8) Anaphora of St Gregory (“Hosanna-liturgy of St Gregory’) (fols. 82ra-86va)&#xD;
III-9) Anaphora of St Jacob of Serug (fols. 86va-91rb)&#xD;
III-10) Anaphora of St Athanasius of Alexandria (fols. 91rb-100rb)&#xD;
III-11) Anaphora of St Basil of Caesarea (fols. 100rb-107vb)&#xD;
III-12) Anaphora of St Cyril of Alexandria (fols. 107vb-113ra)&#xD;
III-13) Second Anaphora of St Gregory (fols. 113ra-115rb)&#xD;
&#xD;
Additiones 1-3.</summary>
